2004-12-05 23:12   Josef Spillner <josef@ggzgamingzone.org>

	* ggzboard/net_reversi.py: - pseudo network handling for Reversi

	  This is the code as used in Escape-SDL, Xadrez-Chines etc...	but
	  in a more object oriented manner, moving the common network
	  handling to two base classes (NetworkBase, NetworkInfo) and only
	  leaving the game-specific details to each game.  These details
	  must then be abstracted for GGZBoard to the lowest common
	  denominator: player names, state, sending and receiving moves...

2004-12-05 22:16   Josef Spillner <josef@ggzgamingzone.org>

